' Deploy Execution Sequence — F1R3Node's current externalized deploy flow
' (in the f1r3node-rust repository).
'
' Source of truth for Figure 3.3 in docs/theory/cost-accounting-migration.md.
' Illustrates F1R3Node's current order-independent cost-accounting strategy:
' each per-term future is spawned via tokio::spawn (reduce.rs:255) with the
' resulting JoinHandles awaited sequentially, and ChargingRSpace wraps every
' produce/consume to apply pre-charge / refund-on-COMM / unified-COMM-cost.
' The cost is deterministic by this strategy
' (rholang/tests/accounting/cost_accounting_spec.rs:323,474 guard this
' empirically). The internalized model proposed in §4 makes the determinism
' machine-checked, removes the per-task ChargingRSpace overhead, and replaces
' the tokio::spawn-per-term + JoinHandle::await pattern with a single
' FuturesUnordered driver (Section 5.4).
'
' End-to-end:
'   Deployer/RNode  -> Evaluator -> CostManager
'                                -> ChargingRSpace -> RSpace (ISpace)
'   Closing the loop: Evaluator queries CostManager for the final cost
'   and returns the deploy result to the Deployer.
'
' Color palette (consistent with fuel-gate-protocol.puml):
'   Actor / Deployer    : salmon        (#F8C3B8)
'   Evaluator (control) : amber         (#FFECB3)
'   Cost accountant     : mint          (#C8E6C9)
'   Wrapper / middleware: teal          (#B2DFDB)
'   Tuple space         : blue          (#BBDEFB)
'
' Semantic arrow colors:
'   Cost charge (fuel out): red-ish     (#C62828)
'   Cost refund (fuel back): green-ish  (#2E7D32)
'
' (LMDB persistence is abstracted behind RSpace; not surfaced here.)
'
' Render:
'   plantuml -tsvg docs/theory/diagrams/deploy-execution-sequence.puml

@startuml deploy-execution-sequence
!theme plain

skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor              #444444
  LifeLineBorderColor     #666666
  ParticipantBorderColor  #333333
  NoteBorderColor         #666666
  NoteBackgroundColor     #FFF8E1
  GroupBorderColor        #333333
  GroupHeaderFontColor    #222222
  DividerBackgroundColor  #ECEFF1
}
skinparam defaultFontName "sans-serif"
skinparam defaultFontSize 12

autonumber

actor       "Deployer / RNode"   as D   #F8C3B8
participant "Evaluator"          as Ev  #FFECB3
participant "CostManager"        as CM  #C8E6C9
participant "ChargingRSpace"     as CR  #B2DFDB
database    "RSpace (ISpace)"    as RS  #BBDEFB

D -> Ev ++ : deploy(P ∣ Q, initial_cost)
Ev -> CM ++ : init(initial_cost)
CM --> Ev -- : ok
note over Ev #FFF3E0
Evaluator spawns each per-term future via
tokio::spawn (reduce.rs:255) — one task
per term. Awaits the resulting JoinHandles
sequentially (reduce.rs:260-269).
end note

group #E3F2FD f₀ — produce(ch_a, d1)  [tokio::spawn'd task]
    Ev -> CR ++ : produce(ch_a, d1)
    CR -[#C62828]->> CM : pre-charge storage_cost_produce
    CR -> RS ++ : space.produce(ch_a, d1)  [interior RSpace sync]
    RS --> CR -- : COMM match → (cont_a, data_a)
    CR -[#2E7D32]->> CM : refund storage_cost_consume (continuation removed)
    CR -[#2E7D32]->> CM : refund storage_cost_produce (datum removed)
    CR -[#C62828]->> CM : charge unified COMM cost
    CR --> Ev -- : match → (cont_a, data_a)
end

note over Ev #E8F5E9
ChargingRSpace::handle_result has applied
the pre-charge / refund / unified-COMM
sequence atomically. The net charge for
this COMM is determined by what was
matched, not by which side triggered it.
end note

Ev -> Ev : eval(body_a)  [dispatched inline by f₀'s tokio task]

group #FFF8E1 f₁ — consume(ch_b, pat, body_b)  [independent tokio task]
    Ev -> CR ++ : consume(ch_b, pat, body_b)
    CR -[#C62828]->> CM : pre-charge storage_cost_consume
    CR -> RS ++ : space.consume(ch_b, pat, body_b)  [interior RSpace sync]
    RS --> CR -- : no match → continuation parked
    CR --> Ev -- : no-match (parked; no event_cost charged)
end

note over Ev : All tokio::spawn'd JoinHandles awaited

Ev -> CM ++ : query total_cost()
CM --> Ev -- : accumulated cost c (deterministic)
Ev --> D -- : deploy result, cost = c

note over D, RS #E8F5E9
Cost is determined by the deploy, not by scheduling.
ChargingRSpace's pre-charge / refund / unified-COMM
strategy makes the externalized model order-independent
(empirically verified by cost_should_be_deterministic at
rholang/tests/accounting/cost_accounting_spec.rs:323).

The internalized model proposed in §4 upgrades this
to a mechanized theorem (ca_cost_deterministic in
Confluence.v), removes the per-task ChargingRSpace
overhead, and replaces this per-term tokio::spawn +
JoinHandle::await pattern with a single FuturesUnordered
driver (Section 5.4) — higher fan-out, completion-order
draining, and short-circuit error propagation via `?`.
end note

@enduml
